            </button>
            <div class="faq-a">
              Yes — in the majority of cases. Research shows that over <strong>90% of disc herniations improve with conservative management</strong> within 6–12 weeks. The disc material is gradually reabsorbed by the body, and nerve inflammation resolves with appropriate treatment including epidural steroid injections, traction therapy, and physiotherapy. Surgery is reserved for the minority of cases where neurological deficits progress.
